        <main>
            <h2>A Simple Financial Calculator</h2>
            <p>This website provides API routes through a Javascript server that function as a simple financial calculator. These calculations can provide: retirement savings based on a monthly savings amount, the amount an investment is worth after some amount of years, and the months left to pay off a loan based on a monthly payment.</p>
            <section>
                <h3>/api/perMonthRetirementSavings</h3>
                <table>
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Parameter</th>
                            <th>Description</th>
                            <th>Example</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>years</td>
                        <td>A number representing the number of years remaining until retirement</td>
                        <td>years=40</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>perMonth</td>
                        <td>A number representing the amount of money that is being saved per month</td>
                        <td>perMonth=280.00</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>interestRate</td>
                        <td>A decimal number representing the interest rate by which savings grows</td>
                        <td>interestRate=0.03 (where 0.03 is 3%)</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <form action="/results/perMonthRetirementSavings" method="post">
                    <label for="ret1">Number of years:
                        <input id="ret1" type="number" name="years" step=1>
                    </label><br>
                    <label for="ret2">Amount saved per month:
                        <input id="ret2" type="number" name="perMonth" step=0.01>
                    </label><br>
                    <label for="ret3">Interest rate:
                        <input id="ret3" type="number" name="interestRate" step=0.01>
                    </label><br>
                    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
                </form>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h3>/api/investedAmount</h3>
                <table>
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Parameter</th>
                            <th>Description</th>
                            <th>Example</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>years</td>
                        <td>A number representing the number of years that an investment has been saved for</td>
                        <td>years=5</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>initial</td>
                        <td>A number representing the value of the initial invesment</td>
                        <td>initial=1000.00</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>interestRate</td>
                        <td>A decimal number representing the interest rate by which the investment grows</td>
                        <td>interestRate=0.08 (where 0.08 is 8%)</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <form action="/results/investedAmount" method="post">
                    <label for="inv1">Number of years:
                        <input id="inv1" type="number" name="years" step=1>
                    </label><br>
                    <label for="inv2">Intial value of investment:
                        <input id="inv2" type="number" name="initial" step=0.01>
                    </label><br>
                    <label for="inv3">Interest rate:
                        <input id="inv3" type="number" name="interestRate" step=0.01>
                    </label><br>
                    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
                </form>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h3>/api/loanPayoff</h3>
